Name: Swagger Petstore
Description: This is a sample server Petstore server.  You can find out more about Swagger at [http://swagger.io](http://swagger.io) or on [irc.freenode.net, #swagger](http://swagger.io/irc/).  For this sample, you can use the api key `special-key` to test the authorization filters.

Endpoints.Name: uploadFile
Endpoints.Description: uploads an image

Parameters.Name: petId
Parameters.Description: ID of pet to update

Parameters.Name: additionalMetadata
Parameters.Description: Additional data to pass to server

Parameters.Name: file
Parameters.Description: file to upload

Endpoints.Name: addPet
Endpoints.Description: Add a new pet to the store

Parameters.Name: body
Parameters.Description: Pet object that needs to be added to the store

Endpoints.Name: updatePet
Endpoints.Description: Update an existing pet

Parameters.Name: body
Parameters.Description: Pet object that needs to be added to the store

Endpoints.Name: findPetsByStatus
Endpoints.Description: Multiple status values can be provided with comma separated strings

Parameters.Name: status
Parameters.Description: Status values that need to be considered for filter

Endpoints.Name: findPetsByTags
Endpoints.Description: Multiple tags can be provided with comma separated strings. Use tag1, tag2, tag3 for testing.

Parameters.Name: tags
Parameters.Description: Tags to filter by

Endpoints.Name: getPetById
Endpoints.Description: Returns a single pet

Parameters.Name: petId
Parameters.Description: ID of pet to return

Endpoints.Name: updatePetWithForm
Endpoints.Description: Updates a pet in the store with form data

Parameters.Name: petId
Parameters.Description: ID of pet that needs to be updated

Parameters.Name: name
Parameters.Description: Updated name of the pet

Parameters.Name: status
Parameters.Description: Updated status of the pet

Endpoints.Name: deletePet
Endpoints.Description: Deletes a pet

Parameters.Name: petId
Parameters.Description: Pet id to delete

Endpoints.Name: placeOrder
Endpoints.Description: Place an order for a pet

Parameters.Name: body
Parameters.Description: order placed for purchasing the pet

Endpoints.Name: getOrderById
Endpoints.Description: For valid response try integer IDs with value >= 1 and <= 10. Other values will generated exceptions

Parameters.Name: orderId
Parameters.Description: ID of pet that needs to be fetched

Endpoints.Name: deleteOrder
Endpoints.Description: For valid response try integer IDs with positive integer value. Negative or non-integer values will generate API errors

Parameters.Name: orderId
Parameters.Description: ID of the order that needs to be deleted

Endpoints.Name: getInventory
Endpoints.Description: Returns a map of status codes to quantities

Endpoints.Name: createUsersWithListInput
Endpoints.Description: Creates list of users with given input array

Parameters.Name: body
Parameters.Description: List of user object
